The paper deals with the problem of finding the k shortest paths in a network, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The application of the problem to routing in real-world networks suggests that it could also fall under the categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also presents theoretical results and simulations, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT).
